<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-288-648  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 288 648.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  March 5 1990 n580 p64(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SPEEA engineers OK Boeing pact. (Seattle Professional EngineeringEmployees Association)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ryan, Margaret.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Seattle Professional Engineering Employees Association (SPEEA)approves a contract with Boeing that provides each Boeing engineerwith three bonuses: a 10 percent bonus, a 5 percent selectiveadjustment pool bonus, and a 4 percent bonus to be paid inDecember, 1990.andP;  The engineers will also receive salary increasesof up to 7 percent, 4 percent and 4 percent over the next threeyears.andP;  The contract offer was approved by a 65 percent to 35percent margin.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Boeing Aerospace Co. (officials and employees).andO;Topic:     Employee RelationsContractsEmploymentBonusSeattle Professional Engineering Employees Association.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>